the top aide to a maryland congressman jumped to 
his death from a hotel window sunday after the washington post 
reported he had made bizarre demands of male staff members 
including asking one to do a striptease 
tom pappas 46 chief assistant to rep roy p dyson fell 18 
stories to a seventhfloor roof of the helmsley palace hotel said 
police spokesman lt stephen davis 
the death appeared to be a suicide davis said pappas left a 
note on hotel stationery he said but he declined to disclose its 
contents 
the post article quoted former staff members as saying dyson had 
ceded control of his washington office to pappas the newspaper 
said pappas used money from dysons reelection campaign to recruit 
for a company pappas owned offering salaries up to 50000 for 
single young men then coerced them to socialize with him 
dyson a 39yearold democrat was registered in a different 
room from pappas sunday at the hotel davis said the congressman 
was interviewed by detectives who would not comment on the 
questioning 
a hotel operator said a roy p dyson was registered but was not 
answering his phone 
dyson was elected to the house in 1980 unseating rep robert a 
bauman a conservative republican who was caught in a scandal when 
the post reported he was seen in public with young male prostitutes 
the posts frontpage article about dyson sunday came as the 
federal election commission investigates allegations his campaign 
disclosure reports concealed 6650 in payments to pappas 
pappas paid 72200 as dysons administrative assistant last 
year also owns a company pappenbauer associates that received 
119642 in fees and expenses since 1980 a revised dyson campaign 
reports shows 
mark frazer republican chairman in dysons district told the 
easton md stardemocrat he filed the complaint that led to the 
fec investigation but it was the post that had raised questions 
about sexual discrimination and what frazer called the apparently 
established preference for young males in the recruiting and hiring 
practices 
the newspaper quoted dyson staff members as saying pappas told 
one male employee that he would have to perform a striptease at a 
1987 office retreat the unidentified aide refused 
scott ourth was quoted as saying that when he was recruited to 
be dysons press secretary in december 1986 he was told he could 
not date for a year and should devote all his time to the office 
ourth quit within six months 
the article also quoted andy hira 22 a special assistant to 
pappas as saying he was fired for refusing to stay at a party in 
dysons annapolis hotel suite last november after dyson announced 
he would run for reelection in 1988 fellow staff member james fox 
quit because of similar demands hira was quoted as saying 
the newspaper quoted a memo from pappas dated nov 14 as saying 
it is important for everyone on this staff to remember that 
tom pappas is the chief of staff responsible for everyones 
paycheck when he expresses a wish however slight it should be 
taken seriously 
those interviewed were quoted as saying they did not believe the 
pressure went beyond attending dinners and parties organized by 
pappas former aides also were quoted as saying pappas excluded 
female staff members from his social activities 
the newspaper said pappas issued a statement saying dysons 
office has been run in an efficient and wellstructured manner 
the office has been managed in a way which has served the people of 
the 1st congressional district of maryland well for many years 
neighbors and former staff members told the post that dyson 
frequently stays at pappas large frame house in accokeek md 
about 20 miles south of washington dysons residence is further 
south in st marys county 
