a world war ii artillery shell that a boy had kept 
in his toy box for six months exploded when he took it out to play 
and police said the blast killed him injured his father and 
destroyed their home 
the japanese imperial army shell exploded on sunday blowing out 
the walls and windows of the boys home in obihiro in northern 
japan 
the boy 9yearold takahiro shibuya died from head injuries 
and his father satomi 38 was injured in the stomach and one hand 
when fragments of the shell hit him as he was walking outside the 
home 
policeman shinobu kusakabe said the boy had kept the rusty 
5by2 inch shell in his toy box since october it not known where 
the boy found the shell 
