guilty of nothing except extremely poor judgment and having 
relationships with the opposite sex which hurt no one 
dunne president of the countys governing board for 19 years 
rejected the associations call that he resign 
there is nothing that i have done over those years that has 
violated the public trust in me he said 
he refused to say whether it was appropriate to hire women after 
having sex with them and told a wmaq reporter who repeatedly asked 
that question youre the scum of the earth and so is the bga 
bga executive director j terrence brunner has admitted that 
as far as we know dunne did not make sex a condition for 
hiring the women 
within two weeks in two instances the people are on the 
public payroll brunner said sunday to me thats an obvious 
link theres no doubt about it 
three of the women dunne allegedly had sex with are on the cook 
county payroll and one used to be the chicago tribune reported 
sunday 
the bga says one of the women who had sex with dunne has been an 
officer with the county forest preserve police since 1984 and 
another was hired by the preserve as a laborer in 1980 
don rose a former political aide to mayors harold washington 
and jane byrne said he doubts dunne broke any laws 
its clear that he simply used his immense hiring powers 
in effect to pass out favors to friends rose said thats not 
illegal but it is exemplary of really terrible abuse of the 
patronage system 
this is the kind of scandal that has brought down 
governments he said however chicago being what it is you 
find more people on the street commenting on his virility at age 75 
than whether or not this was a heinous act 
