<TEXT>
iranian radicals will try to win control 
of irans parliament in a runoff election on may 13 that could 
determine the future course of the islamic revolution 
the staunchly antiwestern radicals made sizeable gains in the 
first round of voting on april 8 for 188 of the 270 seats in the 
majlis or parliament but no faction won a majority the runoff 
will be for the 82 remaining seats 
the results of the first round announced by irans staterun 
media show a tilt toward the radicals with some leading 
conservatives losing their seats 
the radicals could be helped in the runoff by the antiamerican 
passions that resulted after six iranian vessels were destroyed or 
disabled in the persian gulf in battles with the us navy on april 
18 
if the radicals win control of the legislature they could use 
that antiamerican sentiment to adopt an even tougher stand against 
us intervention in the gulf over the next fouryear parliamentary 
term 
tehran radio reported that just under 17 million iranians voted 
in the first round about 80 percent of the electorate 
