pay falling behind the public schools and other reasons the bureau 
system has an annual turnover rate of 33 percent per year among 
principals and 20 percent among all professionals 
among other recommendations the report calls for consideration 
of education loans for prospective teachers with a larger fraction 
forgiven the longer the teacher stays in the system for recruiting 
retired people with valuable knowledge who might like a second 
career and for easing the requirement that indians be given 
preference as principals 
