<TEXT>
about 200 people gathered in a central 
budapest restaurant on may day to form communist hungarys first 
network of activist groups a participant said monday 
the network of free initiatives was formed after 45 dissidents 
issued a petition on march 17 calling for the formation of an 
umbrella organization of independent political ecological 
religious and youth groups in support of democracy in hungary 
we seek to achieve changes in ways already contained in the 
constitution the participant quoted dissident writer janos kiss 
as telling the sunday meeting at the hagi restaurant the 
participant spoke by telephone from budapest on condition of 
anonymity 
speakers at the gathering which included leading hungarian 
dissidents emphasized that the network of free initiatives wants 
to work for change by peaceful means 
the participants elected about 50 representatives to a council 
that will lead the new network in addition to kiss they include 
leading dissident miklos haraszti olympic pentathlete andras 
balczo writer peter esterhazy and historian gyorgy litvan 
also elected were representatives of a youth group and of a 
newly formed independent union of intellectuals as well as members 
of religious and ecological organizations 
the meeting adopted a fourpoint resolution protesting 
government attempts to crack down on the democratic forum a loose 
association of several hundred intellectuals the participant said 
the resolution also protested the recent expulsion of four 
liberals from the communist party the exclusion of independent 
ecology groups from a governmentsponsored environmental 
organization and the death of czechoslovak dissident pavel wonka in 
a czech jail last week the participant said 
sundays statement echoed most of the points introduced in the 
march 17 petition which called on the communist government to 
overcome hungarys current economic and social crisis by engaging 
in dialogue in good faith with representatives of hungarian 
society 
the statement also called for a multiparty parliamentary 
democracy in hungary 
the march document obtained by the associated press appealed 
for good neighborly relations with the soviet union but said 
hungary should remain a sovereign nation as well as an equal 
member of the european family of nations 
the petition has been signed by 726 people since it was issued 
in recent months the number of independent activist initiatives 
has mushroomed in hungary several of these groups have defied 
police warnings and continued to organize meetings 
the participant said the 50member network council would meet 
wednesday night to thrash out a position paper entitled there is 
a way out which reflects the networks views on how to solve 
hungarys current problems 
hungary is burdened by a gross hard currency debt of 16 
billion the highest per capita in the east bloc austerity 
measures introduced by the communist government this year have 
meant widespread belttightening for the countrys 106 million 
citizens 
