crossbreeding between prairie chickens and 
grouse is common but one prairie chicken has taken things a step 
further by courting a brown pickup truck as the object of his 
affections 
he arrived at the jb and pat fischer ranch 23 miles south of 
here in late march and has stayed probably hoping he can convince 
the pickup to agree to a mixed marriage of sorts 
he likes my pickup fischer said he runs toward it 
whenever i drive across the meadow stamps his feet and performs 
his ritual for me i have seen a few grouse near where he stays 
but he tends to ignore them 
prairie chickens boom and grouse dance as they gather 
for their spring courtship rituals which are common to both 
species and are similar prairie chickens inflate large orange air 
sacs on their neck erect tufts of neck feathers and produce a deep 
resonant boom that can be heard for nearly a mile in calm 
weather 
