with up to a foot of snow and sent strong winds gusting through 
much of the rockies and great plains 
the storm centered over southwestern kansas brought rain to 
much of the plains region with thunderstorms hitting central and 
western kansas and central nebraska 
six to 12 inches fell in the palmer lake area north of colorado 
springs colo and up to 11 inches was reported at jelm wyo 
denver reported 2 inches of snow 
parts of the black hills on the western edge of south dakota 
also received up to 8 inches of snow 
a snow advisory was in effect for southeast wyoming with up to 
three inches expected and a warning for high winds and blowing 
snow was in effect for southeast colorado 
winds gusted to 83 mph at la junta colo and to 64 mph at 
colorado springs a tornado touched down in extreme southeastern 
colorado but did no damage 
high winds prevailed from texas to the dakotas amarillo and 
lubbock texas both reported wind gusts of around 45 mph a high 
wind advisory was issued for mountain passes in western texas and 
southern new mexico 
winds gusted to 49 mph at williston nd and at rapid city sd 
rain fell throughout the great plains with about threequarters 
of an inch recorded in broken bow and north platte in central 
nebraska in the six hours ending at 2 pm edt 
rain also fell in western washington and oregon with snow in 
mountain regions a snow advisory was in effect for the cascades in 
oregon with 4 to 8 inches of new snow expected 
patchy light rain hit the north atlantic coast with some heavy 
showers and hail in eastern new york state 
sunshine prevailed over a wide region stretching from the gulf 
coast to the great lakes temperatures rose to the 70s over the 
great lakes and the ohio and tennessee valleys and into the 
mid80s in gulf coast states 
boise idaho had a record low for the date of 23 degrees and 
winnemucca nev tied a record with 19 the nations low was 10 
degrees at yellowstone and jackson wyo 
freeze warnings were issued for the central and northwest 
valleys of new mexico and for southeast arizona above 4000 feet 
at 3 pm edt temperatures ranged from 29 degrees at 
yellowstone wyo to 85 degrees at sarasota fla meridian naval 
air station miss and laredo texas 
on tuesday showers and thunderstorms were forecast to extend 
from arkansas across the central plains to portions of north dakota 
and western minnesota rain and snow showers were forecast to 
linger over the northern and central rockies and the extreme 
western parts of nebraska and south dakota showers were predicted 
from western idaho to the northern pacific coast 
highs in the 40s and 50s were forecast for western portions of 
the northern and central plains the northern and central rockies 
the northern plateau and the pacific northwest highs were 
predicted to be in the 50s in new york state and new england 80s 
from florida and the gulf coast to most of texas and the southwest 
deserts the rest of the nation was forecast to have highs in the 
60s and 70s 
