hours at alliance neb and 186 inches at rapid city sd the 
weather service reported halfinch hail stones fell at sidney and 
alliance neb 
rain also fell over most of western kansas and wind gusted above 
30 mph at dodge city and russell 
high wind blew across the northern plains with gusts exceeding 
50 mph reported throughout the dakotas 
the wind whipped loose topsoil into a dust storm around 
aberdeen sd forcing some drivers to turn on their headlights in 
the middle of the day sunday farmer harry pharis jr of rural 
groton said about 30 acres of newly sprouted barley was cut down by 
the wind and blowing grit 
