<TEXT>
sir hugh rankin who has died at the age of 88 
was an aristocrat turned communist and a man who claimed records in 
pastimes ranging from playing golf to crawling under trees 
his death on april 25 deprived britain of what the daily 
telegraph on monday called an extraordinary character whose 
eccentricity was remarkable even by the rarefied standards of the 
baronetage 
rankins selfcomposed entry in whos who takes up four times as 
much space in that 1972page tome as prime minister margaret 
thatchers 
it is strewn with superlatives ranging from oldest surviving 
member of the 1st royal dragoon guards that fought in ireland in 
192022 to holding an amateur record amongst golfers of great 
britain in having played on 382 separate courses of uk and eire 
rankins pursuits ran from sheepshearing in australia between 
1928 and 1931 to riding bicycles to the top of mountains to 
exploring old roman roads 
wife and himself are only persons who have crawled under dwarf 
fir forest for last mile of most northerly known section of any 
roman road in europe terminating opposite end of kirriemuir golf 
course his whos who entry revealed 
rankin was born in the tunisian desert on aug 8 1899 the son 
of biggame hunter sir reginald rankin 
christened hubert charles rhys rankin he was educated at 
uppercrust harrow high school but ran away to work in a belfast 
shipyard joined the dragoons and became a champion cavalry 
swordsman he received a disability discharge after he was shot by 
a irish sniper 
at 46 he changed his name from hubert to hugh one of several 
such alterations he would make including the addition of omar 
during his moslem period he went from christian to moslem to 
buddhist 
in 1935 he became president of the british moslem society but 
resigned weeks later after a rowdy society meeting they were 
very rude and knew nothing of law and order or methods of 
procedure he was quoted as saying 
from 1944 according to whos who he was a practicing 
nontheistic theravada buddhist who performed holy buddhist 
pilgrimage nov 1944 the second britisher to do so 
rankin served as an army captain in world war ii but according 
to the telegraph regretted fighting for britain saying if a 
revolution comes and come it must after the next world war ill 
do my damnedest to see it succeeds 
in 1950 he was elected to perth county council declaring himself 
a bloodred militant communist in every possible way 
fifteen years later he claimed to be the only baronet living on 
social welfare he said he would take any job except being a 
butler i hate snobbishness 
his first wife helen died in 1945 he is survived by robina 
his second wife 
