firstquarter profit increased to 1639 million or 116 a share 
from 1296 million or 1 a share in the first three months of 
1987 
the figure for the latest quarter includes a onetime special 
credit of 248 million resulting from the sale of two iron ore 
vessels 
the rise in net income occurred despite a decline in 
firstquarter sales to 188 billion from 191 billion a year 
earlier 
the deferral of interest pension and other costs while we are 
operating under the protection of chapter 11 has greatly benefited 
both periods said raymond a hay ltvs chairman and chief 
executive officer the company entered chapter 11 protection from 
creditors in july 1986 
hay noted however that the deferrals of costs and expenses 
have resulted in claims which must be provided for in a plan of 
reorganization before ltv can emerge from bankruptcy 
in january 1987 the federal pension benefit guaranty corp 
terminated and took control of the three pension plans of 
subsidiary ltv steel co assuming financial responsibility for 
23 billion in unfunded liabilities 
but in september the pension agency returned trusteeship of the 
plans to ltv saying it took the step to curb abuse of the federal 
pension insurance program it cited 252 million in profits the 
company reported for the first half of 1987 and ltvs establishment 
of a new pension arrangement for its workers 
ltv has said it believes the agencys attempt to return 
trusteeship of the pension plans is illegal 
